**Learned**: The fix works by adding `|| room.pause.paused` as a fallback to the grace recovery predicate at join-handler.ts:519. This allows tokenless (displayName-based) reconnection to succeed even when the graceTimers map has been cleared by simultaneous-disconnect pause. The edge case occurs because pause entry calls `room.graceTimers.clear()` which removes the timer handles that the tokenless recovery predicate was checking for. The disjunction pattern (check timer OR check pause state) closes this gap cleanly without changing pause semantics.

